#, no-wrap
msgid "Regions: Adding control points\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: Regions-Adding_Point.markdown.txt:5
msgid "[6 of 10](Regions-Deleting_Point.html)"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: Regions-Adding_Point.markdown.txt:8
msgid ""
"The shape of regions in LightZone can be adjusted at any time. This includes "
"adding control points to fine-tune their shape."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title -
#: Regions-Adding_Point.markdown.txt:10
#, no-wrap
msgid "To add a control point to a region:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '1.  '
#: Regions-Adding_Point.markdown.txt:24
msgid ""
"Click the Regions button in the [tool bar](Tools-Controls.html).  (The "
"region kind buttons will appear to the right of the tool bar and the regions "
"for the tool will become visible on your photo.)"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '2.  '
#: Regions-Adding_Point.markdown.txt:24
msgid ""
"![image](images/Region-Add_Point.png) Double-click the region that you want "
"to add a control point to. (The control points will become visible.)"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '3.  '
#: Regions-Adding_Point.markdown.txt:24
msgid ""
"Click on the contour of the region where you want to add a control point: a "
"new control point will be added. You can then drag the new control point "
"until it's in the desired location."
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '4.  '
#: Regions-Adding_Point.markdown.txt:24
msgid "Repeat from step 3 for every control point you want to add."
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '5.  '
#: Regions-Adding_Point.markdown.txt:24
msgid ""
"When done, you can either click anywhere outside the region, or press either "
"the **return** or **esc** (escape) key."
msgstr ""
